<subSubSection id="C36F9F972070FFD720ED8D8685C7FA18" pageId="1" pageNumber="517" type="key">
<keyStep id="3081D4B92070FFD720ED8D8685C7FA18" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">
<paragraph id="8BCACC1C2070FFD720ED8D8685C7FA8D" blockId="1.[151,1437,1186,1414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">
<keyLead id="30846F292070FFD720ED8D8685C7FA8D" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">
1 Scutum usually with pair of narrow stripes, widening at prescutellar disc (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD723CC8D868458FB25" box="[950,1027,1186,1208]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1219,1243]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-20@4.[151,1435,181,1201]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pseudoscelolabes fulvescens (Miller, 1923) A–B: scutum in dorsal view A. Male; B. Female; C. Wing of male. Abbreviations: bm = basal medial cell; br = basal radial cell; cua= anterior cubital cell; CuA = anterior branch of cubital vein; CuA+CuP = anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; dm = discal medial cell; M 1 = first branch of media; M 4 = fourth branch of media; R 1 = anterior branch of radius; R 2+3 = second branch of radius; R = third branch of radius; 4+5 Rs = radial sector." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626841/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); sometimes stripes absent or partially reduced or faint beneath cuticle, or male scutum dark brown with pale lateral margins (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD724688DE4843BFB4B" box="[1042,1120,1216,1238]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1219,1243]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-20@4.[151,1435,181,1201]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pseudoscelolabes fulvescens (Miller, 1923) A–B: scutum in dorsal view A. Male; B. Female; C. Wing of male. Abbreviations: bm = basal medial cell; br = basal radial cell; cua= anterior cubital cell; CuA = anterior branch of cubital vein; CuA+CuP = anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; dm = discal medial cell; M 1 = first branch of media; M 4 = fourth branch of media; R 1 = anterior branch of radius; R 2+3 = second branch of radius; R = third branch of radius; 4+5 Rs = radial sector." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626841/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites usually pale brown with narrow darker anterior margin (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD722078DF982BCFB6F" box="[637,743,1245,1267]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-123@3.[151,1435,381,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pseudoscelolabes fulvescens (Miller, 1923) A–B. Lateral habitus A. Male; B. Female; C–D. Anterior view of frons. C. male; D. female; E. Antenna of male in lateral view; F. Hind femur of male in anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Figs 1A, B</figureCitation>
); surstyli with basal width nearly as long as length in posterior view (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD7250F8DF9815BFA8D" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1652,1676]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,194,1629]" captionTargetId="figure-23@5.[151,1435,181,1629]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pseudoscelolabes fulvescens (Miller, 1923) male terminalia. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Right lateral view; D. Left lateral view; E. Surstyli in posterior view. F. Hypandrium in left lateral view; G. Hypoproct and subepandrial sclerite in dorsal view. Abbreviations: bac scl = bacilliform sclerite; cerc = cercus; epand = epandrium; hypd = hypandrium; hyprct = hypoproct; ph = phallus; sbepand scl = subepandrial sclerite; sur = surstylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626843" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626843/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); eyes of females separated by width of anterior ocellus (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD7235E8DDE8335FA8D" box="[804,878,1274,1296]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-123@3.[151,1435,381,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pseudoscelolabes fulvescens (Miller, 1923) A–B. Lateral habitus A. Male; B. Female; C–D. Anterior view of frons. C. male; D. female; E. Antenna of male in lateral view; F. Hind femur of male in anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
).......... 
<taxonomicName id="4C75B79F2070FFD723868DDE85C7FA8D" authority="(Miller, 1923)" baseAuthorityName="Miller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1020,1436,1274,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Pseudoscelolabes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvescens">
<emphasis id="B901100E2070FFD723868DDE854BFA92" box="[1020,1296,1274,1295]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Pseudoscelolabes fulvescens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE4B1ED2070FFD725668DDE85CEFA8D" author="Miller, D." box="[1308,1429,1274,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="517" pagination="437 - 464" refId="ref6498" refString="Miller, D. (1923) Material for a monograph on the Diptera fauna of New Zealand: Part III family Empididae. Transactions of the New Zealand Institute, 54, 437 - 464." type="journal article" year="1923">Miller, 1923</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCACC1C2070FFD720ED8C3C85C7FA18" blockId="1.[151,1437,1186,1414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">
<keyLead id="30846F292070FFD720ED8C3C85C7FA18" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">
- Scutum with broad, brown presutural supra-alar and postsutural supra-alar spots, separated or narrowly fused (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD7255F8C3C85CAFAB0" box="[1317,1425,1303,1326]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1969,1993]" captionTargetBox="[206,1392,869,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-268@7.[196,1392,869,1945]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pseudoscelolabes lesagei Sinclair &amp; Barros sp. nov. A–B. Lateral habitus A. Male holotype; B. Female paratype; C. Habitus of male holotype in dorsal view; D–F. Habitus of female in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Figs 5C–F</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites yellow, with anterior half broadly brown with medial extension posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD724098C118486FAD6" box="[1139,1245,1333,1355]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1969,1993]" captionTargetBox="[206,1392,869,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-268@7.[196,1392,869,1945]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pseudoscelolabes lesagei Sinclair &amp; Barros sp. nov. A–B. Lateral habitus A. Male holotype; B. Female paratype; C. Habitus of male holotype in dorsal view; D–F. Habitus of female in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626849/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Figs 5C–F</figureCitation>
); surstyli with basal width shorter than length in posterior view (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD722F78C768287FAF5" box="[653,732,1362,1384]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1499,1523]" captionTargetBox="[210,1382,257,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-305@8.[210,1382,257,1486]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pseudoscelolabes lesagei Sinclair &amp; Barros sp. nov. terminalia of male holotype. A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Left lateral view; D. Surstyli in posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626851/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
); eyes of females closely approximated, similar to males, to slightly narrower than width of anterior ocellus (
<figureCitation id="134ED0992070FFD722328C5482C9FA1B" box="[584,658,1392,1414]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-123@3.[151,1435,381,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pseudoscelolabes fulvescens (Miller, 1923) A–B. Lateral habitus A. Male; B. Female; C–D. Anterior view of frons. C. male; D. female; E. Antenna of male in lateral view; F. Hind femur of male in anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="517">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
)..................... 
